<P>> I have to agree with Benign on the first part about the mana thing, i dont care much for that, in wars it seems the warriors are back first, last night our guild was fighting, and there was a monk who most have been binded like real close because i know we killed him at least twice, but he would come right back hehe. But i disagree with the whole exp loss thing, why whould you want to turn this game into another uo. Stat loss sucks there, no one cares for it other than the people who dont pvp at all,. I dont see how if they lost exp it would be any less popular, and looting i still think should be just stuff in the bags, and the money on them. Im level 24 now and i make pretty good cash were i hunt, but after looking at the prices of plate, 900 or so plat for just one piece, i just dont see ever risking taking that out to the field,. You would be and open target, warriors like i said are already walking banks. Most true players vs. players dont care about the loot rather that they do the actual battle itself. But there is always the few out there that kill just well to ruin your fun no other reason.,

</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
